Documentation;

For a good SNOBOL4 tutorial look in the Catspaw "vanilla snobol"
distribution.

doc/snobol4.1
	man page for snobol4 (uses (ANY('nt') 'roff') -man macros)
	only describes changes from the "green book".

doc/snobol4.0
	text formatted output of snobol4 man page

doc/snobol4.html
	WWW HyperText formatted output of snobol4.1

doc/snobol4.ps
	PostScript formatted output of snobol4.1

doc/ports.doc
	status of ports to various systems.

doc/porting.doc
	information on porting to a new system,
	particularly the usage of Makefile variables and m4 macros.

doc/porting.ps
	porting information in PostScript.

TODO.soon
	current top priority tasks (hopefully small in any release)

TODO
	older identified tasks / wish list.

See the Catspaw vanilla.arc or vanilla.tar for a DOS/PC port of
	SNOBOL4, many demo programs, SNOBOL4 language documentation,
	and ordering information for books & products from Catspaw!

